We can rewrite the given quotient as follows:
\begin{align*}
\frac{2.430}{3.0} \times \frac{10^{6}}{10^{2}} &= 0.81 \times 10^{6-2} \\
&= 0.81 \times 10^{4}
\end{align*}

To express the answer in scientific notation, we need to write the first number as a value between $1$ and $10$. Thus, we can rewrite $0.81$ as $8.10 \div 10$ or $8.10 \times 10^{-1}$. Therefore,
\begin{align*}
0.81 \times 10^{4} &= 8.10 \times 10^{-1} \times 10^{4} \\
&= 8.10\times 10^{3}
\end{align*}

Therefore, the quotient in scientific notation is $8.10\times 10^{3}$.

